# Pre-commit hook — runs on every `git commit`.
#
# 1. ESLint auto-fix: fixes what it can; exits non-zero (blocking the commit)
#    if any errors cannot be fixed automatically.
# 2. Prettier reformat: rewrites files to match .prettierrc.
# 3. git add -u: re-stages files that were modified by the fixers above so the
#    commit contains the cleaned-up versions rather than the originals.
#    Note: `git add -u` stages ALL modifications to tracked files, including
#    any changes you intentionally left unstaged. If you need finer control,
#    consider adopting lint-staged (https://github.com/lint-staged/lint-staged).

npm run lint:fix || exit 1
npm run format:write
git add -u
